<div class="topic-content col-sm pr-lg-60">

	    <!--[BEFORE-ARTICLE]--><!DOCTYPE HTML><span class="marker before-article"></span><section id="ref1" data-level="1"><p><strong><span id="ref216513"></span>Bill Gates</strong>, in full <strong>William Henry Gates III</strong>,  (born October 28, 1955, <a href="https://www.britannica.com/place/Seattle-Washington" class="md-crosslink autoxref">Seattle</a>, <a href="https://www.britannica.com/place/Washington-state" class="md-crosslink autoxref">Washington</a>, U.S.),  American <span id="ref932732"></span><a href="https://www.britannica.com/technology/computer" class="md-crosslink">computer</a> programmer and <a href="https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/entrepreneur" class="md-dictionary-link md-dictionary-tt-off" data-term="entrepreneur">entrepreneur</a> who cofounded <span id="ref662868"></span><a href="https://www.britannica.com/topic/Microsoft-Corporation" class="md-crosslink">Microsoft Corporation</a>, the world’s largest personal-computer software company.</p><!--[P1]--><span class="marker p1"></span><!--[AM1]--><span class="marker AM1 am-inline"></span><script type="application/ld+json">
